data.name: Cold Summer Borscht
data.quickTastyDescription: A refreshing chilled beet soup that's vibrant and full of flavor, perfect for hot summer days.
detailedCookingInstructions: Prepare the beets by cooking and grating them, or using pre-cooked beets to save time.
In a large bowl, combine the grated beets, diced cucumber, sliced radishes, chopped green onions, and dill.
In a separate bowl, mix the plain yogurt, vegetable broth, and lemon juice until smooth.
Pour the yogurt mixture into the bowl with the veggies and stir well to combine.
Season with salt and pepper to taste. Adjust the consistency with more broth if necessary.
Chill in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes before serving to enhance the flavors.
